  "chapter": {
    "number": 56,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Salvation for Foreigners"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Maintain justice and do what is right,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for My salvation is coming soon,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and My righteousness will be revealed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blessed is the man who does this,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the son of man who holds it fast,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who keeps the Sabbath without profaning it",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and keeps his hand from doing any evil.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let no foreigner who has joined himself to the LORD say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“The LORD will utterly exclude me from His people.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And let the eunuch not say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am but a dry tree.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "For this is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“To the eunuchs who keep My Sabbaths,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who choose what pleases Me",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and hold fast to My covenant—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will give them, in My house and within My walls,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a memorial and a name",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "better than that of sons and daughters.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will give them an everlasting name",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that will not be cut off.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And the foreigners who join themselves to the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to minister to Him,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to love the name of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to be His servants—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "all who keep the Sabbath without profaning it",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and who hold fast to My covenant—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will bring them to My holy mountain",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and make them joyful in My house of prayer.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Their burnt offerings and sacrifices",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be accepted on My altar,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for My house will be called a house of prayer",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2715
          },
          {
            "text": "for all the nations.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus declares the Lord GOD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who gathers the dispersed of Israel:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will gather to them still others",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "besides those already gathered.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Sinful Leaders"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Come, all you beasts of the field;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "eat greedily, all you beasts of the forest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Israel’s watchmen are blind,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are all oblivious;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they are all mute dogs,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they cannot bark;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they are dreamers lying around,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "loving to slumber.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like ravenous dogs,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are never satisfied.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They are shepherds with no discernment;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they all turn to their own way,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "each one seeking his own gain:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Come, let me get the wine,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let us imbibe the strong drink,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and tomorrow will be like today,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "only far better!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
